HEADWORD: Orthoclase
<hw>Or"tho*clase</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Ortho-</ets> + Gr. <?/ to break.]</ety> <fld>(Min.)</fld>
<def>Common or potash feldspar crystallizing in the monoclinic system
and having two cleavages at right angles to each other. See
<er>Feldspar</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

